A warm welcome to Chinese President Xi Jinping by Chinese Americans in SF!🇨🇳🇺🇸 #APEC2023 

Retired Judge Julie Tang said: “Chinese Americans are proudly welcoming President Xi. And the young people who are among us will carry this image for a long time to come. Chinese Americans can overcome many atrocities, quash anti-Asian hate as long as US and China enjoy peaceful coexistence. Today we pin the hope on these two leaders, and the will of the people for peace.”

🧵A "basketball diplomacy"? 

In 1970s, Ping-pong diplomacy laid the groundwork for diplomatic ties between 🇨🇳China & 🇺🇸the U.S.
Now basketball diplomacy seems playing a role in stabilizing ties.
Californian govenor @GavinNewsom gave President Xi a Golden State Warrior jersey as a gift ahead of the welcome dinner in the U.S.

result.text:
How much do 🇺🇸American students know about 🇨🇳China?
I went to UC Berkeley for a vox-pop.

I found out that most don't know much about China.
But these young students are probably among the most open-minded, willing to accept different cultures.
Hope there'll be more exchanges between students in the US & China to boost communications & understanding.
